The paper deals with learning embeddings of directed networks with text associated nodes, which is a problem that falls under the scope of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses neural networks, which is a common technique in deep learning (DL), and hence cs.DL (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also deals with network analysis, which falls under the scope of social network analysis (SNA) and information retrieval (IR), and hence cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed algorithms against various baselines, which is a common practice in machine learning and data mining (DM), and hence cs.LG (Machine Learning and Data Mining) is also a likely sub-category.
